## Preconditions: 
1. Put the check-mark on the "Open Flutter Inspector view on app launch".
2. "Disable tracking widget creation locations" check-mark must be UN-CHECKED.

## Steps to Reproduce
1. Run the "main.dart" file via clicking on the "Run" button. 
2. Wait till the "Run" will be finished & Flutter Inspector bar automatically opens.

Expected result: FLutter Inspector shows the "Widget tree" of an application.
Actual result: FLutter Inspector does not show the "Widget tree" of an application.

I have a problem with the widget inspector both inside VS Code and in the browser. With complex views, the widget inspector only shows the top app widget and the app bar - the body/content is gone. When i open a simpler view, the body/content is visible again.
Any chance you have a repro you can share with us?
I'm also getting this with the latest version of IntelliJ and the Flutter/Dart plugins... :(
I did a flutter clean and its start working again

This helped me get it back to work in VSCode.

1. Stop the emulator if you are running the app.
2. Run `flutter clean` in your terminal
3. Run the app again.
4. Open Command Palette in VS Code by pressing `F1`
5. Search for `Dart: Open Dev Tools` and click enter
6. Click `Open Widget Inspector Page`

The Widget Inspector will now display the Widget Tree.

The widget tree is showing although the feature I liked was when I could tap on the widget and see the exact widget in the code not only in the widget tree
Is there a way to fix this ?
Thanks
